      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Slice your <strong>aubergine[s]</strong> in half lengthways, keeping the green stalk[s] on, then score the<strong> </strong>flesh in a criss-cross pattern</p><p>Add the <strong>aubergine half[ves]</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 15 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1583490143394-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1583490143394-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1583490143394-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1583490143394-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1583490143394-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the aubergine is cooking, peel and chop your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Cut your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> lamb mince</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until browned all over, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1583490150879-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1583490150879-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1583490150879-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1583490150879-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1583490150879-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve <strong>half</strong> your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and your<strong> tomato paste</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>ground cumin</strong> to the lamb with your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> dried oregano</strong> and a grind of <strong>pepper</strong>, then cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the<strong> tomato stock</strong> and reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for 15 min or until thickened and the lamb is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>Turkish-style</strong> <strong>lamb stew</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1583490154768-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1583490154768-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1583490154768-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1583490154768-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1583490154768-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the aubergine has had an initial 15 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven and press the<strong> </strong>flesh down firmly with a fork to release the juices (this will help it cook quicker!)</p><p>Add the <strong>tomato </strong>and<strong> onion wedges </strong>to the tray[s] with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 15 min further or until the aubergine flesh has softened and everything is tender – these are your<strong> roasted vegetables</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1583490159174-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1583490159174-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1583490159174-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1583490159174-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1583490159174-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve the <strong>remaining beef stock mix</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> in a large bowl</p><p>Add your<strong> couscous</strong> to the bowl with the beef stock, stir it all together, then cover with a tea towel and set aside until all of the stock has been absorbed</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1583490163725-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1583490163725-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1583490163725-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1583490163725-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1583490163725-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the aubergine is tender, scoop the <strong>softened flesh</strong> out of the skin, discard the skin</p><p>Tip: Carefully hold the stalk (it will be hot!) to scrape the flesh out easily!</p><p>Chop the<strong> scooped aubergine flesh </strong>finely</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1583490168652-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1583490168652-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1583490168652-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1583490168652-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1583490168652-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped aubergine flesh</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(not a big garlic fan? Try using less!), your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Stir it all together – this is your <strong>aubergine yoghurt</strong></p><p>Fluff the <strong>couscous</strong> with a fork</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1583490172743-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1583490172743-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1583490172743-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1583490172743-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1583490172743-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>aubergine yoghurt</strong> over the<strong> fluffed couscous</strong>, then top with the <strong>Turkish-style</strong> <strong>lamb stew</strong> and <strong>roasted vegetables</strong></p><p>Garnish with a good grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
